node.text:
The Warbird Roundup was a amazing show but for Staff Sergeant Paxton McCamish, one of our avionic specialists, it was extra memorable. It allowed him the opportunity to visit his hometown of Boise, Idaho.
.
Check out this video to hear firsthand from SSgt McCamish and his mother Cassandra about their experience with the team! 
.
.
🎥 | Staff Sergeant Thomas Barley 
.
@warhawk.air.museum @aircombatcommand @usairforce 
.

node.text:
Thank you Michigan! 🤘⚡️

Our “why” for coming to air shows is simple.  It’s all of YOU. You all keep our spirits high throughout our air show season. 

We love to entertain, educate and inspire, so if you ever see us at a show don’t hesitate to come up and say hi! 

That being said, we want to hear from you! What is your “why” for coming to air shows? Let us know in the comments! 

#F35DemoTeam | @thunderovermichigan | @airforceheritageflight 

🎥: @thomasbarleyphoto 
.
.
.
.
.

Thought we’d try something a little different with this recap video and hide a little surprise in the music🇺🇸😎

The past weekend up in the #pacificnorthwest have been amazing. Two shows. One weekend. And the first time we’ve flown the demo for Northwest Washington. 

Can anyone tell what our music choice was?

🎥: @codie.trimble l #F35DemoTeam
.

node.text:
Have you had the chance to go to one of our air shows yet? 

Whether you’re a die-hard aviation enthusiast or wanting to teach your family about the subject, air shows are a great way to have fun and educate yourself about the world of aviation.

Shout out to the Thoreson family for letting us follow you around @dekeslaytonairfest to make this video! 

Check out the link in our bio for our air show schedule and we hope to see you at one soon! ✈️🤟🏽
.
🎥: Staff Sergeant Thomas Barley 
.
.
. 
@aircombatcommand l @usairforce 
.
.
.

node.text:
Our mission is to recruit, engage and inspire the next generation of leaders. While flying at air shows is amazing, the people and communities we meet with make it all worth it.

Were looking foward to meeting you all this weekend, May 22-23, at the Atlanta Air Show, so dont hesitate to come up to us and say hi! 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
During the time between air shows, we like to take it as a time to reflect and look back. To see how we can use the past to make the future better.

2020 was an insane year, for a lot of different reasons, and it made our first year as an @aircombatcommand Demo Team one to remember.

Who knows what 2021 will bring, but we're hoping that at the very least, it means more air shows and more chances to showcase this team to the world. 

If you told us two years ago where we'd be now, we wouldn't have believed you. Thanks for all of your support, and thanks for 200K.

We're proud to call ourselves your @usairforce F-35A Lightning II Demonstration Team.

📹: @codie.trimble 
#F35DemoTeam l #ReadyAF l #AimHigh

Coming to an airshow is a special experience for all of us, and to be able to perform for people around the world is a privilege and an honor.⁣
⁣

⁣
We'll see you soon Canada for @airshowlondon 🇨🇦.⁣

node.text:
Ever Upwards ☝️
⁣
With over 2,600 cars in attendance, being able to perform for the @newyorkairshow massive drive-in audience was definitely one of the highlights of this season.⁣
⁣
We're constantly amazed at the love and passion for flight that we see at every show.⁣
⁣
If you missed us, here's a small look at our airshow experience.⁣
⁣
🎥: Staff Sgt Tompkins l #F35DemoTeam⁣

node.text:
Views from #the6ix

What. A. Show. Canada!

That's a wrap for the annual Canadian International Air Show! This one will definitely be one for the history books. 

It was great to get a chance to fly alongside our friends with the @cfsnowbirds and the @cf18demoteam 🇺🇸🇨🇦🙌.

To all of our neighbors up north, thank you for your hospitality, your friendship, and your support. It was our honor to fly for you.

Till next time🤘⚡⚡

📸: Capt Kip Sumner & Staff Sgt Thomas Barley

#F35DemoTeam l #Canada🇨🇦

One more time Toronto!

Today's the last chance to come see us in the skies of Ontario at the @ciastoronto air show!!

You've been amazing Canada 🙌🇨🇦, with views like this, we wish we could stay longer! 

Be sure to check out the live-stream if you can't make it out! (link in bio).

node.text:
Bringing #5thgen aviation to #the6ix

It's the first day of the @ciastoronto air show!

Judging by this shot from yesterday's rehearsal, we think this weekend's show is going to be pretty mind-blowing 😎.

If you can't make it out to see us, no worries! You can check out how to live-stream show at the link in our bio.

See you soon Canada 🇨🇦🤟

#F35DemoTeam l #TorontoAirShow

📷: @usairforce Capt. Kip Sumner

node.text:
Heads up! 👀

We're flying north of the border this week to perform at the Canadian International Air Show in Toronto, Ontario, this Sept. 4-5!

After how @airshowlondon went last year, we couldn't wait to get back to Canada and showcase more of what the F-35 is capable of!

Stay tuned for flight times, live-stream info, and for more general info about the show, check out @ciastoronto

See you soon Canada 🇨🇦🤘

#F35DemoTeam l #Torontolife

📸: Capt Kip Sumner

node.text:
The Warbird Roundup was a amazing show but for Staff Sergeant Paxton McCamish, one of our avionic specialists, it was extra memorable. It allowed him the opportunity to visit his hometown of Boise, Idaho.
.
Check out this video to hear firsthand from SSgt McCamish and his mother Cassandra about their experience with the team! 
.
.
🎥 | Staff Sergeant Thomas Barley 
.
@warhawk.air.museum @aircombatcommand @usairforce 
.

node.text:
Thank you Idaho! ✈️🤘🏽

It was a pleasure to bring the future of aviation to the Warbird Roundup this weekend and fly in a heritage flight with two P-40 Warhawks.

Big thank you to everyone who came to support us and huge thank you to all of the warbird pilots of the past. Our team wouldn’t be here today without you! 
.
.
📸 | @thomasbarleyphoto 
. 
.

node.text:
Thank you Michigan! 🤘⚡️

Our “why” for coming to air shows is simple.  It’s all of YOU. You all keep our spirits high throughout our air show season. 

We love to entertain, educate and inspire, so if you ever see us at a show don’t hesitate to come up and say hi! 

That being said, we want to hear from you! What is your “why” for coming to air shows? Let us know in the comments! 

#F35DemoTeam | @thunderovermichigan | @airforceheritageflight 

🎥: @thomasbarleyphoto 
.

node.text:
Bringing Lightning to @thunderovermichigan

Talk about a PHENOMENAL show Michigan! Our team will be talking about this one for a while. Swipe 👉 through this post and we think you’ll see why.

We’re headed home for a small break and then we think it’s time we took it international 👀🇨🇦.

See you soon Canada!!!

#F35DemoTeam

📸: Capt Kip Sumner & SSgt Thomas Barley

node.text:
Tearing through the sky

We apologize in advance for those who come to watch us fly, we know it can be hard to see our jet when it’s covered in vapor 😏. But don’t worry, we’ve got you covered. 

We’ve got one more day at the @thunderovermichigan air show, so fingers crossed we get the same amount of vapor as we did yesterday 🤞🤞.

📸: Capt Kip Sumner
